“It is a game changer,” said Trump legal advisor Alan Dershowitz who along with Kushner promoted the plan to Trump.
Currently, Title VI prohibits discrimination on the basis of race, color and national origin.
By declaring Judaism a nationality rather than religion, it puts it under the rubric of federal protection, unlocking all sorts of tools for the school to shut down speech.
Nevertheless, the order as being reported will allow the federal government to force schools to restrict protests and monitor speech and curriculum in the classroom.
Trump’s order would make the IHRA (International Holocaust Remembrance Alliance) definition of anti-Semitism the official guideline for Title VI.